snippet: McDonald's is cutting back, selling more restaurants to franchisees, and slashing costs in a plan light on details, but heavy on promises to turn around the business. Bobbi Rebell reports.
headline: McDonald's putting itself on a diet

snippet: McDonalds tests new cafe in Sydney where quinoa salad replaces burgers and fries. Julie Noce reports.
headline: McDonalds tries healthy approach

snippet: McDonald's is cutting back, selling more restaurants to franchisees, and slashing costs in a plan light on details, but heavy on promises to turn around the business. Bobbi Rebell reports.
headline: McDonald's putting itself on a diet

snippet: McDonald's decision to phase out human antibiotics from its chicken supply is part of the fast food chain's efforts to please customers looking for more natural ingredients, but it still falls short of rivals' policies. Bobbi Rebell reports.
headline: McDonald's latest  health move

snippet: McDonalds tests new cafe in Sydney where quinoa salad replaces burgers and fries. Julie Noce reports.
headline: McDonalds tries healthy approach

snippet: The chain said that within two years its domestic restaurants would no longer use birds treated with antibiotics “important to human medicine.”
headline: McDonald’s Moving to Limit Antibiotic Use in Chickens

snippet: The Williamstown Theater Festival in Massachusetts will include that Eugene O’Neill drama, as well as the world premieres of a William Inge play, “Off the Main Road,” and “Paradise Blue,” a drama by Dominique Morisseau.
headline: Audra McDonald and Will Swenson to Star in ‘A Moon for the Misbegotten’ in Williamstown

snippet: A day after nationwide protests, the company said it was raising wages at least $1 over the local minimum wage at the restaurants it operates. Franchise outlets may feel new pressure.
headline: McDonald’s to Raise Pay at Outlets It Operates

snippet: Mr. Gibbs, who left the White House in 2011, will join McDonald’s as global chief communications officer.
headline: McDonald’s Hires Robert Gibbs, Ex-Press Secretary for Obama

snippet: As fast-casual chains soar in popularity, the iconic burger chain is under pressure. A well-known food expert and a designer have some ideas for improvement.
headline: A Visit to McDonald’s, Celebrity Chef in Tow

snippet: Steve Easterbrook, chief branding officer, will take over from Don Thompson after one of the chain’s worst financial performances in years.
headline: As Sales Dip, McDonald’s Is Replacing Don Thompson as Chief
